{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":190487,"duration_api_ms":221990,"num_turns":27,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"ef324b08-d29d-4f19-8e60-c6163215ba31","total_cost_usd":1.1890979999999998,"usage":{"input_tokens":3776,"cache_creation_input_tokens":65299,"cache_read_input_tokens":900526,"output_tokens":4247,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":65299,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":3776,"outputTokens":4247,"cacheReadInputTokens":900526,"cacheCreationInputTokens":65299,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.98343675,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":129,"outputTokens":14356,"cacheReadInputTokens":469185,"cacheCreationInputTokens":69467,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.20566125000000002,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"In `safe_plan_hash_backfill` (fs.rs ~line 3395), the call site in the `update_task_run` open-entry finalization path calls `safe_plan_hash_backfill` AFTER setting `entry.plan_hash` from the caller's explicit value (line 3389: `entry.plan_hash = Some(plan_hash.to_owned())`). This means `safe_plan_hash_backfill` will always short-circuit on `entry.plan_hash.is_some()` when the caller supplied a plan_hash. This is correct behavior. However, there is a subtle ordering issue: `safe_plan_hash_backfill` checks `entry.outcome.is_terminal()` to skip terminal entries, but it is called on line 3395 BEFORE `entry.outcome = outcome` is set on line 3396. Since this code path is inside the `else` branch (meaning the entry is NOT yet terminal — it's being transitioned TO terminal), the `is_terminal()` check will see the old Running outcome, which means the terminal guard in `safe_plan_hash_backfill` is vacuous here. The backfill still proceeds correctly because the entry is about to become terminal, and this is exactly when you'd want the last chance to backfill. Document this ordering dependency with a brief inline comment so future refactors don't reorder the calls and break the invariant.","rationale":"The correctness of `safe_plan_hash_backfill` in the finalization path depends on being called before `entry.outcome = outcome`. If someone refactors and moves the outcome assignment above the backfill call, the terminal guard would cause backfill to silently stop working for all completions — a subtle regression with no compile-time or test-time signal. A one-line comment prevents this."},{"body":"The `unique_terminal_replay_match` contract enforcement (fs.rs ~line 2839) uses `AppError::CorruptRecord` for what is actually an internal programming invariant violation (caller passed `(Some(run_id), None)` for started_at). `CorruptRecord` implies corrupt on-disk data. Consider using a distinct error variant or at minimum adjust the error message prefix to say 'internal contract violation' rather than naming the ndjson file, since the file is not corrupt — the caller violated the API contract. This matters for error triage: an operator seeing 'CorruptRecord' in logs may investigate the data file rather than the calling code.","rationale":"Using the wrong error variant makes debugging harder in production. When operators see CorruptRecord they inspect and potentially 'repair' the data file. A contract violation means the calling code has a bug, not the data. The fix is a one-line change to the error variant or message."}],"summary":"Reviewed all changes across src/adapters/fs.rs, src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs, and src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs. All 683 tests pass, clippy is clean. The three issues from the project prompt are addressed correctly: (1) Journal detail structs are unified — duplicate structs in fs.rs eliminated, shared canonical structs from model.rs used for both ser/deser with round-trip tests. (2) Runless-to-named completion now accepted with started_at disambiguation, runtime contract enforcement replaces debug_assert, and the terminal replay matcher also guards on started_at. (3) plan_hash auto-population uses snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation provenance tracking with safe evolution detection, correctly skips terminal replays, and handles snapshot read failures gracefully. Two minor issues found: an ordering dependency between safe_plan_hash_backfill and outcome assignment that should be documented, and a misleading error variant for an internal contract violation."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"825a47dc-7f7c-4c9c-93d4-bfada0a2f6f6"}
